                id = "1", speaker = "Doctor Sallow",
                text = "*(He edges sideways, maintaining his exclusion zone.)* People call me a coward. *(defensively, from six feet away.)* They say, Sallow, a *real* doctor tends the sick! And I say — yes, and a real doctor *catches what the sick have* and *dies*, and then there's *no* doctor, and how is *that* the moral high ground? *(he waggles a gloved finger.)* I have outlived four \"brave\" physicians this season. FOUR. They tended the harvest-fever hands-on, nobly, and now they're nobly *dead*, and the quarter has *me*, shouting cures from across the road, *alive.* *(quietly, the bluster wavering.)* ...It doesn't feel like winning, though. Standing across the road. Watching them cough. Knowing the brave thing and doing the *living* thing. It doesn't feel like winning at all.",
