            g.nodes.Add(new DialogueNode
            {
                id = "fail", speaker = "Doctor Sallow",
                text = "*(He stops edging away. For a long moment the beaked mask just stares.)* ...Oh. *(very quietly.)* You've — that's not the fever I'm afraid of, is it. *(he lowers the pomander.)* It's the *failing.* If I stay across the road, then when they die, it's the *fever's* fault, the *harvest's* fault, *anyone's* fault but mine. But if I *go to them*, if I *try* — and they die anyway, the way the harvest-marked always die — then I'll have *failed them, personally, with my hands.* *(his voice cracks behind the beak.)* And I'm not — I became a doctor to *win*, and you can't win against the harvest, and I'd rather be a live coward than a healer who held a dying child and *couldn't.* *(a shaking breath.)* You've named it. Gods. The mask was never for the fever. It was so I wouldn't have to see their faces when I lost. ...I don't know if I'm brave enough to take it off. But you've made me ashamed enough to consider it. That's a start. That's more than four brave dead men managed to give me.",
                autoNextNodeId = "close",
