            {
                id = "teach", speaker = "Doctor Sallow",
                text = "*(He brightens, then brightens *more*, an idea taking him.)* Teach. *(he taps the beak.)* I can't touch the sick — but I *know* things, I know more medicine than the four dead heroes combined, that's *why* I'm not dead, I'm not just a coward, I'm a *well-informed* coward! *(he's pacing now, in his little exclusion zone.)* I could train the brave ones! The ones who *will* go close — give them the cures, the precautions, the things the dead doctors learned too late — *(he stops.)* — and then their courage and my cowardice make *one whole physician*, and the quarter gets tended by people who *won't* die of it because I taught them how not to! *(he laughs, giddy.)* A coward who makes ten brave healers! That's — that's a way to be *useful* and *alive*, which I'd given up hoping were the same direction. You've just reconciled my two strongest instincts. Do you know how rare that is? Off you go. I've a school to start, from a safe distance.",
